# Browser MCP

Operational notes for interacting with web UIs via Chrome MCP or Playwright.

- Chromium uses `~/.pki/nssdb`, not the system CA bundle — after the README's `update-ca-certificates`, also import the server cert into NSS so MCP browsers stop firing cert-error toasts on every refresh:
  ```bash
  certutil -d sql:$HOME/.pki/nssdb -D -n tbe-demo-localhost 2>/dev/null
  certutil -d sql:$HOME/.pki/nssdb -A -t "C,," -n tbe-demo-localhost -i server-ssl-cert.pem
  ```
  Re-run when the server cert rotates (SHA1 from `openssl s_client -connect localhost:8443 ... | openssl x509 -noout -fingerprint -sha1` no longer matches the NSS entry).
- Chrome MCP refs are snapshot-local. Any state change between snapshot and click (the previous click, a
toast, a modal close, a network response settling) can renumber them. Re-snapshot immediately before each
click whose neighborhood may have moved.
- Don't `click_ref` icon-only buttons. Multiple "+", "⋮", "×" in one view are indistinguishable in the
a11y tree. Use `eval` to find the nearest labeled anchor (heading text, field label) and click the button
scoped to it.
